But educated in a very liberal way (different from most US Lutherans, as I've found):<br>
<br>
Humbly trying to understand, what somebody in modern society with modern problems and modern world views can do with the bible; recognizing all its difficulties and oddities;  taking into account the world views of antiquity, different text layers and contradictions contained in it. <br>
Mainly scholarly approach, not spiritual. But still acknowledging that I personally am not satisfied to live in a world where only the rules of natural science are existant.<br>
No focus on daily use of bible and prayer; no focus to spread the belief, unless somebody *really* wants to hear it.<br>
<br>
Weird? That's what I'm used to. And I'm happy with it. The older I grow the more.<br>
