<br>
I celebrate the holidays of the majority of the society that I've been brought up with.  Christmas, Easter, Hallowe'en, etc.  They're not religious days for me, but I like the tradition.  Especially Christmas songs; I love to sing them.  And, um, the other two I listed have chocolate.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
For awhile in my teenage years, I learned about Wicca from my brother, but it just really wasn't for me.<br>
<br>
In a way, I sort of see every religion as looking at a facet or facets of a higher power.<br>
<br>
I think it more important to live a good life than to be pious in a religion.  I can't believe that there would be a God that would punish people for not believing in Him even if they were really nice people, or at least if there was, I'd consider Him pretty stuck up.  I also can't think of why just about any *ahem* consensual acts between adults should be considered sins.<br>
<br>
I pretty much think that anything's fine as long as you're not hurting anyone.  Though I suppose the religious upbringings of some people would have them feel that some things that I would accept are actually hurtful, which I think is fine as long as they don't push their standards of behavior on me - worship how you want, and the way you feel comfortable, the way you feel a connection with your higher power.<br>
<br>
Or if you're not feeling it, don't worship.  That's fine, too. <p><div align="center"><center><img src="http://www.members.shaw.ca/vae/velsig.jpg"><BR>
