<br>
Interesting note on the &quot;religions are evil&quot; argument:<br>
<br>
I'm an historian and my specialty is actually the Early Catholic church (I was the altar boy who thought the tortured saint statues were the coolest thing ever).  One thing I've learned from this is that Religions, despite their good aims, are run by men and men are naturally fallible.  Any organized religion has characteristics very similar to that of a Political Machine.  They usually have well-meaning goals, but it's not unheard of to have some bozo in a position of power who makes some ill-advised decisions.  It's never as black and white as &quot;the church is evil&quot; or &quot;the church is great!&quot;<br>
<br>
Wassily<br>
